This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for reasoning tasks, which are typically covered under the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of memory networks and dynamic selection of relevant memory candidates also suggests a possible connection to neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories.
